A week after they revealed their preliminary agreement, the two banks explained that MUFG was going to buy 9.9% of Morgan Stanley common stock at a single price of $25.25, a total amount of $3 billion.
The agreed price is 19% lower than the book value of the securities as at 31 August.
MUFG is investing an additional $6 billion in convertible securities, which provide a 10% return and have an exchange price of $31.25.
Morgan Stanley said the entire operation would be based on an average unit price of $29, or 28% below its current exchange rate.
